result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer J. Lafernier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: Repeater], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Obtain stable housing acceptable to her agent.  Defendant to be subject to random testing by her agent.

ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Sebion.  Victim notification complied with.  Victim is present.  Court concerned that probation is being offered again.  State advised that the defendant has been accepted into Trempealeau County's treatment court.  Attorney Sebion spoke.  Court wants a PSI.  She can plead today.  Defendant plead no contest to counts 1 and 2 as a repeater.  Court recited the charge and possible penalties she plead to.  Joint recommendation for probation.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  She understood.  Felony warnings given.  Court confirmed the prior criminal conviction.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.  Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights. Court found that a factual basis exists for the pleas.  Found guilty of counts 1 and 2.  PSI ordered due 12/11.  SEH set for 12/21/15 at 10:30 am.  Bond continued.
